Package alphacare

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlphaCare
    Class that is called when the application first starts, will call other classes.
    CreateAccountView
    View that allows a user to create a new account to join the service.
    LoginCntrl
    Controller that handles a user logging in or if new, creating an account.
    LoginView
    View that prompts the user to enter their credentials to log in.
    MenuModel
    Model of a menu that will show different options depending on the type of user that has logged in.
    MenuView
    View of a main menu that will show different options to users that have logged in.
    PatientListController
    Controller that will handle lists of patients that a medical professional has access to.
    PatientListModel
    Model that holds the list that holds different patients.
    PatientListView
    View that will show patients to user that has access to those particular patients.
    PatientModel
    Model that will hold information on a patient.
    PatientRecordsView
    View that will show a particular patient's records.
    PatientView
    View that will show a high level view of a patient.
    ProfileView
    View that will show profile information of the logged in user.
    RecordListModel
    Model that will hold a list of different patient records.
    RecordView
    View that allows user to see a particular record and its details.
    StaffModel
    Model that will hold information on medical staff.
    TwoFactorView
    View that will prompt the user about and show information on two factor authentication.
    UserCntrl
    Controller that will handle information related to different types of users and the views that show that information.
    UserListModel
    Model that will hold a list of application users.
